The article argues that health policy in the US should focus on more than just expanding insurance coverage through the Affordable Care Act (ACA). It states that while health insurance provides financial protection, it has less of an impact on health than other factors such as drug abuse, diet, physical activity, and smoking. The article suggests that the government should address these determinants of health and the opioid crisis, rather than solely focusing on expanding insurance coverage. It also emphasizes the need for innovation to lower healthcare costs and drug prices while still promoting incentives to innovate.